description:
Moritaka and Akito's hard work is paying off, and they start challenging their rival Eiji's popularity in Shonen Jump. But just as they plan to take the next step, the team is hit with a surprising setback. Moritaka and Akito will need the help of their manga artist friends to overcome this hurdle!

Chapter Titles

  • Ch. 44: Repayment and Inversion
  • Ch. 45: Illness and Motivation
  • Ch. 46: Loving Gaze and Cooperation
  • Ch. 47: Discrepancy and Reason
  • Ch. 48: Life and Death and Stationary
  • Ch. 49: Recall and Call
  • Ch. 50: Recklessness and Guts
  • Ch. 51: Restart and Low Rank
  • Ch. 52: Suggestions and Rush
name: Recklessness and Guts

description: Mizuki’s neighbor Shinnosuke returns from college for a visit, but the championship boxer is surprised to find the girl he likes involved with someone else. Will Akira be able to compete for Mizuki’s affections against such a manly rival?
name: Vol. 2

description: Tula is a neat and picturesque town on the Ukrainian-Russian border. But under its neutral surface, the town’s hiding many underground levels filled with the labs of Temsek, the diabolical chemical and warfare factory directed by Lord Marsden. The deeper you go, the worst is the horror. That doesn’t scare our heroic trio, ready to plunge to the bottom of the abyss, to break all hell loose inside their enemies’ hidden HQ!
name: Sfida alla Temsek

description: The picture of a mysterious faceless demon appeared inside one of the qanats, the old Arab canals that run under Palermo. A little while later, the speleologist who find the picture is found dead. And bloodless! Sent by Caleb to investigate, Harlan immediately finds himself immersed in the suffocating and shady atmosphere of the Sicilian capital city, among hot-bloodied puppeteers as the likable Salvo and misanthropic old nobles like Baron Ajovalasit. Inside the Baron’s run-down mansion there is a famous “sirocco room”, cooled by underground currents, where Harlan will discover something horrible...
name: La camera dello scirocco

volume.name: Flash Gordon: Invasion of the Red Sword

description: Martin was invited by his uncle Paul Mystère to investigate the strange apparitions in the village of a dear friend. Among comedy and surreal situations , once again , as always in summer , Martin has to deal with Altrove , Dee & Kelly , and Angie , this time in England.
name: L'impareggiabile Reeves

description: Collects Strange #1-6.
Translates Avengers: Earth Mightiest Heroes #1-8.
name: Año Uno

description: What else is there to fear but FEAR ITSELF? A nuclear-bomb-equipped Hellicarrier stolen by a terrorist sleeper cell and docked over New York City is probably a good candidate. Wolverine and Melita race against the clock to shut down STRIKE before STRIKE takes out half of the city!
name: Part 2

description: I, Librarian The astonishing story of the incomparable Rex Libris, Head Librarian at Middleton Public Library, and his unending struggle against the forces of ignorance and darkness. With the aid of an ancient god who lives beneath the library branch, Rex travels to the farthest reaches of the galaxy in search of overdue books. He must confront incredible foes, such as powerful alien warlords who refuse to pay their late fees. Wearing his super thick bottle glasses, and armed with an arsenal of high technology weapons, he strikes fear into recalcitrant borrowers, and can take on virtually any foe from zombies to renegade literary characters.
name: I, Librarian

description: Rex's preparations for a book retrieval mission to Benzine V are interrupted by crisis in the library. A hapless patron has become lost in the labyrinth of literature and only Rex can save her from certain doom, for amidst the shelves of books lurks a terror, a hideous, malefic entity whose unspeakable purpose can only be guessed at! To top things off, Rex must try to settle the ruffled feathers of his room mate, Simonides, a former philosopher who is now a small budgie. And finally, a new librarian, who bears an evocative name for Rex, joins the library staff.
name: Labyrinth of Literature

description: Rex performs his first leap from orbit, only to find that he has gone from the frying pan into the fire. Hostile aliens on the surface of Benzine V attack our hero as soon as he lands, and a desperate fight for survival breaks out. Back at the library, Circe and Hypatia get to know each other over a plate of fresh, home baked cookies. The tranquility is interrupted by a wave of hysterical patrons fleeing from the Montgomery reading room. It has been overrun by unknown hostile forces, and only Circe can bring the situation under control and prevent the chaos from spilling over into the rest of the library.
name: Leap of Faith

description: Rex's efforts to find a diplomatic solution to the confrontation with the Snowmen of Benzine V are dealt a serious blow when Simonides gets control of a loaded firearm. The situation is further complicated by the arrival of Vaglox's armed and irritable minions. Back on earth, an energy manifestion of blood thirsty Vandals is intent upon burning Middleton library, and all within, to the ground. Only Circe stands between them and their horrific, biblioclasmic goal.
name: Battle on Benzine!

description:
In his first story arc on the new GREEN ARROW series (collected in GREEN ARROW: QUIVER), fan-favorite writer/director Kevin Smith (Clerks, Dogma, Jersey Girl) resurrected the legendary DC hero to huge critical and popular success. He followed it up with the work collected in GREEN ARROW: THE SOUNDS OF VIOLENCE — a harrowing 128-page trade paperback stylishly rendered by Phil Hester & Ande Parks. This volume collects GREEN ARROW #11-15, including the original painted covers by Matt Wagner, and features an introduction by Hester and a special sketchbook section showcasing his and Parks' dynamic art.

This graphic novel puts Oliver Queen and his closest loved ones directly in the madman's bullseye. Plus, the relationship between Ollie and his son/successor Connor Hawke is explored, while Mia — the young girl whom Green Arrow saved — flirts with becoming a new "Speedy." Also, Ollie rekindles his romance with Dinah Lance, a.k.a. Black Canary!
name: TPB

volume.name: Green Arrow: The Sounds of Violence

description: With the aid of his Avengers allies, Marc Spector is one step closer to finding out who the kingpin of the super-powered LA underworld is, but the kingpin is one step closer to finding out all of Moon Knight's secrets. From the Eisner award-winning team that brought you Daredevil, Spider-Woman and Halo is another gorgeous chapter in the brand-new mythos of Moon Knight.

Inspector Ishida makes his long-awaited return in this classic-style whodunit! Ishida and the rabbit ronin are escorting a killer to trial when a storm forces them to take refuge at a roadside inn. The inn's other guests include a court noble and his entourage, a paper merchant and his daughter, and a quiet samurai, all driven there by the rains. When one of them is murdered during the night, it's up to Inspector Ishida and Usagi to solve the mystery.
name: Murder at the Inn, Part One

description: With shape shifters, vampires, spirits and drunks hot on their tail, Sargent and Mei make a daring escape. But are they headed towards salvation or something much worse...
name: Book 4

description: The deadly finale brings all the exposed threads together and Green Wake's secrets are revealed. Morley must face his own demons to find Babylon, and vile monsters stalk his every step to keep him from his final destination: Home.

Sean nears the end of his first journey. He will soon learn that friends can just as easily become enemies. The boy's genetic gift begins to take hold amidst the innumerable obstacles. A warrior is born...

name: A Dark Oz Special

description: After barely surviving the disaster at the Seven Stars, Sean returns to his new, improved life as a key member of the Daomu. However, his past, and the pasts of those he trusts, are about to come crashing down around him. The truth is closer than he could possibly imagine...

Driven to discover the truth regarding his father's mysterious death years prior, Melvin Reyes seeks to prove the existence of Spontaneous Human Combustion after fresh outbreaks of the phenomenon reveal a pattern only he can see, a predictability model only he can read, and the terrifying realization that whatever phenomenon consumed his father is also boiling inside of him, just waiting for release...
name: Combustible

description: Bayville town has a Spontaneous Human Combustion problem. But whereas 'Kelvin' Melvin has always seen a supernatural, almost darkly spiritual phenomenon at work, would-be muckraker, Emily, sees a conspiracy that's anything but divine. Can they work together to uncover the truth, or will they be consumed by the fire?
name: Kelvin Melvin

description:
100,000 years before the time of John Carter! Barsoom is a dying world: its once mighty oceans are receding and its atmosphere grows more tenuous by the day.

Tak Nan Lee is an environmental scientist who sees the future doom of life on Barsoom unless the atmosphere can be maintained by a life-giving air filter plant. His idea is to make the atmosphere safe for every inhabitant on the planet. However, an evil Jeddak is setting decrees that will limit who receives the precious oxygen and thus ensure the extinction of whole races.

On a routine mission, Tak Nan Lee intercepts a terrible battle between the Green Hordes and the emerging Red Martians. The green warriors are driven away, but virtually every red warrior is found slain. As the scene closes, an injured red woman is discovered. Tak Nan Lee approaches her, but can he truly help her in her condition?
name: The Tide of Battle

volume.name: Warlord of Mars: Fall of Barsoom

description: What if the one that got away kept coming back? Norm Raymer, an aspiring comic artist, has a turbulent relationship with Maggie. With their passionate ups and downs, is this love, or merely youthful lust? For better or worse, Norm and Maggie must discover whether or not they can ever really make it as a normal couple. Can you really be a normal couple when your whole life is just fodder for your comic book? A new romantic comedy graphic novel for young comic nerds in love.
name: A True Love Story

description: The young man who will be the Red Skull struggles to stay alive, as the martial drumbeat of Berlin's forces of evil grows in power. Johann's life is a hardscrabble fight and a miserable existence...hunger, thievery, scrapping with street gangs...until he wins the affections of a friendly shopkeeper and his daughter. But if a boy raised himself on the streets through violence, can there be any other way but tragic destiny?
name: Incarnate, Part 2

description: Haven't picked up Irredeemable yet? Now is your chance as a brand new arc is set to begin in this multiple Eisner and Harvey Award-nominated series. The Plutonian has gone from a Mad God wreaking havoc on the world to a captured denizen of an intergalactic insane asylum. Legendary comic writer Mark Waid continues this rollercoaster of a saga with an issue that's new reader friendly and sure to shock longtime fans. Don't dare miss this epic superhero comic that is redefining the genre!

'HARD LABOR' Conclusion! About to give birth and on the run from mutants, demons and gods alike, Wolfsbane turns to the only ones she feels she can trust: her own kind. But even with the help of THE PACK, will Wolfsbane and her baby survive the ordeal? And considering some believe the baby to be the harbinger of the end of the world, do we even want them to?

The Archie Americana Series is a series of comic book trade paperbacks, published by Archie comics from the early 1990s to the present. The series attempts to present a history of Archie comics, with each book featuring significant stories from a specific decade, and featuring introductions by famous writers and celebrities.
name: Best of the Forties

description:
Straight from the far reaches of Hell, comes a collection of classic Hellraiser tales that will light your soul on fire! This must-have collection features stories originally published by Marvel Comics - classic spinetinglers for die-hard fans and new readers alike, collecting a host of work form comic luminaries that you will not want to miss! Featuring the work of Clive Barker (Hellraiser), Neil Gaiman (Sandman), Mike Mignola (Hellboy), Alex Ross (Kingdom Come), Kevin O'Neill (League of Extraordinary Gentlemen), and many more!

This new collection by BOOM! Studios collects the best stories from the classic Hellraiser anthology series released by Epic Comics from 1989 to 1993.
name: Volume One

description: Good Apollo, I'm Burning Star IV, Volume One: From Fear Through the Eyes of Madness is a single-issue graphic novel in the Amory Wars storyline by rock band Coheed & Cambria front-man Claudio Sanchez. The story of Good Apollo takes a step outside the science fiction narrative of the first three chapters (of the Amory Wars series) and examines the life of The Writer, a character who is crafting the lives of the protagonist Claudio and his companions in the form of a fictional story. Through a series of delusional conversations with his ten speed bicycle about an unfaithful former lover, The Writer decides he must kill the Prise Ambellina to properly end his story. The events in the narrative itself build up to a final confrontation between Jesse's rebel forces and the Red Army of Supreme Tri-Mage Wilhelm Ryan under the command of General Mayo Deftinwolf, as well as a literal meeting of the Writer and Claudio culminating in the death of Ambellina and Claudio's emergence as the Crowing.
name: Good Apollo, I'm Burning Star IV, Volume One: From Fear Through the Eyes of Madness

volume.name: Good Apollo, I'm Burning Star IV, Volume One: From Fear Through the Eyes of Madness

description: Translates X-Men: Emperor Vulcan #1-5.
Translates X-Men: Phoenix Warsong #1-5.

volume.name: 100% Marvel: X-Men: La Canción de Guerra de Fénix

description: Translates X-Men: Age of Apocalypse #1-6 & X-Men: Age of Apocalypse One Shot.

volume.name: 100% Marvel: X-Men: Retorno a la Era de Apocalipsis

description: Contains : X-Men/Spider-Man #01-04.

volume.name: 100% Marvel Best: L'Uomo Ragno: Finchè le Stelle non si Spegneranno

description: Translates 1602 #1-4.
name: Donde las Cosas Comienzan a Cambiar

description: Translates 1602 #5-8.
name: Donde se Pantea una Traición

description: Translates Iron Man #7-12.

volume.name: 100% Marvel: Stan Lee Visita el Universo Marvel

description: Bart tells Ralph Wiggum a tale of comic book mail-order products gone awry, while Lisa teaches Homer a cautionary lesson about the good and bad effects of going green. Also, 'Maggie's Crib.'
name: Mail-Order Mayhem!; Maggie's Crib; Planet of the Plants
